{
  "video_id": "Zg5ex8WZUao",
  "title": "What is the difference between civil cases and criminal cases?",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 900.0,
      "end_time": 3380.0,
      "text": "It wouldn&#39;t make sense for a defendant in a contract dispute"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3380.0,
      "end_time": 7689.0,
      "text": "to have the same kind of trial as, say, Jason."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7689.0,
      "end_time": 9230.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why the courts in this country"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9230.0,
      "end_time": 11710.0,
      "text": "split cases into two categories--"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11710.0,
      "end_time": 13880.0,
      "text": "civil and criminal."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13880.0,
      "end_time": 16940.0,
      "text": "A civil case is when one person, the plaintiff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16940.0,
      "end_time": 19200.0,
      "text": "brings legal action against another person who"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19200.0,
      "end_time": 23240.0,
      "text": "has allegedly wronged them-- the defendant-- with the intent"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23240.0,
      "end_time": 25209.0,
      "text": "of collecting damages."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25210.0,
      "end_time": 28700.0,
      "text": "Damages equals money."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28700.0,
      "end_time": 31500.0,
      "text": "A criminal case is where a government prosecutes someone"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 31500.0,
      "end_time": 33740.0,
      "text": "to prove them guilty of committing a crime,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 33740.0,
      "end_time": 35400.0,
      "text": "like a car thief."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35400.0,
      "end_time": 37210.0,
      "text": "The victim of this crime is often"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 37210.0,
      "end_time": 39910.0,
      "text": "a witness in the government&#39;s case against the accused,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 39910.0,
      "end_time": 42430.0,
      "text": "as well as any eyewitnesses."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 42430.0,
      "end_time": 44660.0,
      "text": "In a civil case, the court can judge"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 44660.0,
      "end_time": 46339.0,
      "text": "that a defendant owes the plaintiff"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 46340.0,
      "end_time": 49200.0,
      "text": "money, or other property, or must perform"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 49200.0,
      "end_time": 51800.0,
      "text": "a service that was promised."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 51800.0,
      "end_time": 52930.0,
      "text": "Mostly, though, it&#39;s money."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 52930.0,
      "end_time": 56730.0,
      "text": "Reimbursement, compensation, or punitive damages."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 56730.0,
      "end_time": 60169.0,
      "text": "However, a judge in a civil case cannot send a defendant"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 60170.0,
      "end_time": 62210.0,
      "text": "to jail, barring a few exceptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 62210.0,
      "end_time": 64670.0,
      "text": "usually regarding the intentional violation of court"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 64670.0,
      "end_time": 65970.0,
      "text": "orders."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 65970.0,
      "end_time": 69390.0,
      "text": "In a criminal case, either the prosecutor or a grand jury"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 69390.0,
      "end_time": 71330.0,
      "text": "initiates the proceedings."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 71330.0,
      "end_time": 73330.0,
      "text": "Punishment for guilty defendants can"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 73330.0,
      "end_time": 75720.0,
      "text": "range from fines, community service,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 75720.0,
      "end_time": 80539.0,
      "text": "or educational classes, to much more serious consequences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 80540.0,
      "end_time": 82290.0,
      "text": "such as jail time."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 82290.0,
      "end_time": 84880.0,
      "text": "And anyone, including the defendant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 84880.0,
      "end_time": 88140.0,
      "text": "can be called as a witness in a civil case,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 88140.0,
      "end_time": 91350.0,
      "text": "whereas in a criminal case, they cannot be forced to."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 91350.0,
      "end_time": 94179.0,
      "text": "Also, criminal cases generally have a higher burden"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 94180.0,
      "end_time": 96380.0,
      "text": "of proof than civil cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 96380.0,
      "end_time": 99570.0,
      "text": "This is mainly because a person&#39;s freedom is at stake."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 99570.0,
      "end_time": 102624.0,
      "text": "Prosecutors have to work that much harder to show guilt."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 102624.0,
      "end_time": 104390.0,
      "text": "They must prove that the defendant"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 104400.0,
      "end_time": 106320.0,
      "text": "is guilty beyond a reasonable doubt."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 106320.0,
      "end_time": 108170.0,
      "text": "A plaintiff in a civil case, however,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 108171.0,
      "end_time": 109670.0,
      "text": "only needs to prove that they should"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 109670.0,
      "end_time": 112570.0,
      "text": "win by a preponderance of the evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 112570.0,
      "end_time": 115899.0,
      "text": "Preponderance just means the greater amount, or weight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 115900.0,
      "end_time": 118620.0,
      "text": "of the evidence when taking into account"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 118620.0,
      "end_time": 121690.0,
      "text": "the believability of that evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 121690.0,
      "end_time": 123800.0,
      "text": "For more details on the differences between types"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 123800.0,
      "end_time": 127920.0,
      "text": "of cases, or anything having to do with court in any way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 127920.0,
      "end_time": 131130.0,
      "text": "Legal You is your go-to resource."
    }
  ]
